There are thousands of reasons to get rid of the Corporate Average Fuel Economy (CAFE) program - as many as 4,500,
to be exact. As UpDate readers know, CAFE, which requires a minimum fuel economy for a given fleet of passenger cars or
trucks, provides no real environmental benefits, but it does kill people! !
Anticipating a Department of Transportation move to increase CAFE standards on light trucks, the House of Represe
tatives passed a provision to freeze CAFE for one year at current levels in the appropriations bill (27.5 mpg for passenger cars,
20.7 for light trucks). CEI is now working to get Congress to abolish the standard entirely.
Presented below are CEI's state-by-state estimates of 1994 passenger car deaths due to CAFE. Figures are based on the
1989 Harvard-Brookings study, which calculated a 14 to 27 percent increase in passenger car deaths due to auto downsizing
caused by CAFE. The figures below represent the high-end estimate.I
